description: After a healthy snack for the kids? Try these crispy veggie stars. They're packed with carrots and are a fun way to get the kids to eat their vegetables.

name: Veggie stars Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Grease and line a large baking tray with baking paper.
Place carrot, cheese and egg in a food processor. Process for 30 seconds or until smooth. Add flour and pulse to combine.
Lightly dust a clean work surface with flour. Press out dough until 5mm thick. Using a 6.5cm star-shaped cutter, cut stars from dough. Re-use scraps and cut stars to make a total of 18 stars.
Transfer stars to tray, leaving a 1.5cm space between shapes. Bake for 15 minutes or until crisp and lightly golden. Stand on tray for 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool. Serve.
